HEADWORD: Intransgressible
<hw>In`trans*gress"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intragressibilis</ets> that can not be crossed. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Transgress</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being
transgressed; not to be passed over or crossed.</def>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intransient</ent>⟦br⟧
